news.title: Sanghi Industries to raise upto Rs 2,200 crore
news.para: The RPS shall carry a preferential right vis-à-vis equity shares of Sanghi Industries, with respect to the payment of dividend and repayment in case of winding up or repayment of capital.

news.title: New real estate projects decline in Gujarat in FY24
news.para: Gujarat's real estate market witnessed a slowdown in new project launches during FY 2023-24, attributed to factors like rising construction costs, incomplete projects, online shopping impact, and investors shifting to stocks.

news.title: Shops to rentals, business blooms in Jewar as many move in from other places
news.para: Jewar's economy booms with the new airport, driving land deals and rentals. Local entrepreneurs like Virendra Kumar and Himanchal Sharma seize business opportunities.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers acquires about 1,073 sq meters land in Mumbai for Rs 33.10 crore
news.para: Rahul Rajan Jesu Thomas, whole time director of Suraj Estate Developers said, "The acquisition enhances our sales potential by Rs 120 crores, strengthening both the company's project pipeline and its financial outlook."

news.title: Companies now investing in premium office fit-outs
news.para: Savills India data reflects a shift towards premium spaces, while tech players like Tushar Mittal drive demand amidst a growing construction industry.

news.title: Lavasa creditors invoke Darwin Platform Infrastructure's guarantee
news.para: Creditors invoked a guarantee due to CIRP non-compliance, halting the Lavasa project. Legal battles continue as lenders lose confidence in the resolution applicant. NCLT and NCLAT petitions are pending, with DPIL seeking more time.

news.title: China's Landsea Green Management misses offshore notes redemption
news.para: Landsea has joined a growing list of Chinese developers facing a lack of liquidity because of a sustained fall in the value of property in the country.

news.title: About 721 acres land deals closed in Jan-Mar, nearly 3,000 acres in FY24: Anarock
news.para: ​During the entire 2023-24 fiscal, property consultant Anarock said that real estate developers and other entities have closed 101 land deals, cumulatively accounting for 2,989 acres.

news.title: Oberoi Realty sales bookings down 53% to Rs 4,007 crore in FY24
news.para: In a regulatory filing on Saturday, Oberoi Realty informed that the company sold 228 units worth Rs 1,775 crore in the fourth quarter of the last fiscal year. It sold 4.49 lakh square feet of carpet area.

news.title: Verify labourers at all construction sites in Goa, cops told
news.para: The DGP’s move comes in the aftermath of the recent rape and murder of a five-year-old girl in Vasco, allegedly by labourers.

news.title: UltraTech Cement acquires grinding unit from India Cements; announces expansion
news.para: ​In a stock exchange filing, UltraTech said its board has approved acquisition "of a grinding unit having installed capacity of 1.1 million tonnes per annum in addition to a captive railway siding at Parli, Maharashtra from The India Cements Limited... for a consideration of Rs 315 crores".

news.title: Hong Kong regulator to investigate PwC auditing of China Evergrande Group
news.para: Heavily indebted Evergrande has become a symbol of the years-long crisis in China's property market, and last month its onshore unit was accused of a $78 billion revenue overstatement.

news.title: SHF urges Maharashtra to cut premium to 5% to make government land freehold
news.para: Chairman of State Housing Federation Suhas Patwardhan told TOI that they have been demanding a reduction in premium, but that the government has kept it at 10%.

news.title: Noida's Trident Realty raises Rs 1,200 crore through sale of assets
news.para: The company plans to use the proceeds to strengthen its residential portfolio, as it has lined up projects worth ₹15,000 crore for launch in 2024-25.

news.title: HCC Rs 350 crore rights issue oversubscribed 2.5 times
news.para: ​The company, in a statement, said it has retained an amount of Rs 350 crore, corresponding to 100 per cent of the rights issue size, with the balance being refunded to investors.

news.title: Sundream Group to invest Rs 250 crore in Noida project
news.para: The newly-announced investment is over and above the first phase investment and the construction for the second phase has begun, according to a statement.

news.title: Yes Bank founder gets bail, walks out of jail after four years
news.para: ​​The property belonging to Avantha Realty Ltd (ARL) was already mortgaged for a loan taken by the company from Yes Bank. It was purchased for Rs 378 crore -- against the market value of Rs 685 crore -- by Bliss Abode Private Limited, run by Rana Kapoor's wife Bindu Kapoor, in 2017.
